HEADWORD: Omnivorous
<hw>Om*niv"o*rous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>omnivorus</ets>; <ets>omnis</ets> all + <ets>vorate</ets> to eat
greedily. See <er>Voracious</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>All-devouring;
eating everything indiscriminately; <as>as, <ex>omnivorous</ex> vanity;
an <ex>omnivorous</ex> intellect</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>,
<def>Eating both animal and vegetable food.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p> -- <wordforms><wf>Om*niv"o*rous*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Omo-</ent>⟦br⟧
